http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/New-Mandya-SP-assumes-office/article13982705.ece

C.H. Sudheer Kumar Reddy, an IPS officer of the 2010 batch, assumed charge as Mandya Superintendent of Police on Tuesday. He replaces Bhushan Gulabrao Borase, who served as SP of the district since February 2013.Mr. Reddy, a B.Tech graduate from Pondicherry Engineering College, is a native of Narsaraopet in Guntur district in Andhra Pradesh. He served as Additional Superintendent of Police in the communally sensitive Bhatkal in Dakshina Kannada district, and later as SP of Bidar district.Mr. Reddy took the charge from Mr. Borase, who was transferred to Bengaluru as SP of the Criminal Investigation Department (Cyber Crime).